ZH: 狗咬了我的手。
EN: The dog bit my hand.

ZH: 小孩咬了一口苹果。
EN: The child took a bite of the apple.

ZH: 这只蚊子咬得我好痒。
EN: This mosquito bite is so itchy.

ZH: 老鼠咬了一个洞穿过了衣服。
EN: The mouse bit a hole through the clothes.

ZH: 猫咬了我的电线！
EN: The cat bit my wire!

ZH: 鲨鱼咬了我的潜水装备。
EN: The shark bit my scuba gear.

ZH: 我的弟弟咬了我一口。
EN: My little brother bit me.

ZH: 这个馒头里有一颗牙印，看来是被人咬了。
EN: There is a teeth mark on this steamed bun, looks like it was bitten by someone.

ZH: 蚂蚁咬了我的脚趾。
EN: The ant bit my toe.

ZH: 鸟咬了我的头发做巢。
EN: The bird bit my hair to make a nest.

ZH: 他看上去像是边喝酒边咬烟。
EN: He looks like he is drinking and smoking at the same time.

ZH: 这家伙非得要看到血才肯松口。
EN: This guy won't let go until he sees blood.

ZH: 你为什么老咬我耳朵啊？
EN: Why do you keep biting my ears?

ZH: 这隻蚊子咬的地方肿了。
EN: The spot where the mosquito bit me is swollen.

ZH: 这条鱼咬勾了，快把它拉上来！
EN: The fish took the bait, reel it in quickly!

ZH: 小偷咬掉了钻石项链上的钩子。
EN: The thief bit off the clasp of the diamond necklace.

ZH: 他总是喜欢咬腿。
EN: He always likes to bite legs.

ZH: 你别总咬手指！
EN: Stop biting your fingers all the time!

ZH: 狼非常凶猛，可能会咬你。
EN: Wolves are very fierce, they might bite you.

ZH: 这种蚊子特别厉害，一咬就起大块红肿。
EN: This type of mosquito is particularly aggressive, it leaves big red swellings when it bites.
